Current African Boxing Union featherweight champion, Waidi “Skoro” Usman is set to battle Azinga “Golden Boy” Fuzile in South Africa for the vacant International Boxing Federation (IBF) Continental Africa Super Featherweight Title on Sunday. The title fight is the main bout of Rumble Africa Promotions bill and will hold at the Orient Theatre in East London. Usman has suffered only two losses in 14 fights since turning pro in 2011, while Fuzile is undefeated after 10 fights. Usman knocked out Kenyan Michael Nyawade in the 11th round at the National Stadium, Lagos in April to become the African Boxing Union featherweight champion. 22-year-old South African, Fuzile turned pro in 2014 and is a former South African, World Boxing Council Youth and IBF Continental Africa featherweight champion.